@startuml MessageQueue

title High-Level Design: Message Queue / Async Messaging

skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam componentStyle rectangle

' ─── Producers ───
package "Producers" {
    component [Order Service] as prod1 #D5E8D4
    component [Payment Service] as prod2 #D5E8D4
    component [User Service] as prod3 #D5E8D4
}

' ─── Message Broker ───
rectangle "Message Broker\n(Kafka / RabbitMQ / SQS)" as broker #DDEEFF {
    queue "Topic / Queue\norder.created" as q1
    queue "Topic / Queue\npayment.processed" as q2
    queue "Dead Letter\nQueue (DLQ)" as dlq
}

' ─── Consumers ───
package "Consumers (Consumer Groups)" {
    component [Notification Service] as con1 #FFF2CC
    component [Inventory Service]    as con2 #FFF2CC
    component [Analytics Service]    as con3 #FFF2CC
    component [DLQ Processor /\nAlert Service] as con4 #F8CECC
}

database "Consumer\nOffset Store" as offset #EEE

' ─── Flow ───
prod1 --> q1 : publish order.created
prod2 --> q2 : publish payment.processed
prod3 --> q1 : publish user.registered

q1 --> con1 : subscribe (push/pull)
q1 --> con2 : subscribe
q2 --> con3 : subscribe

q1 --> dlq  : retry exhausted → DLQ
q2 --> dlq  : retry exhausted → DLQ
dlq --> con4 : manual / alert processing

con1 --> offset : commit offset
con2 --> offset : commit offset
con3 --> offset : commit offset

note right of broker
  **Patterns:**
  • Point-to-Point (Queue) — one consumer
  • Pub/Sub (Topic)        — many consumers
  • Competing Consumers    — scale out consumers
  • Fan-out                — copy to multiple queues

  **Guarantees:**
  • At-most-once  delivery (may lose)
  • At-least-once delivery (may duplicate)
  • Exactly-once  delivery (hardest, Kafka txns)
end note

note right of dlq
  **Dead Letter Queue:**
  Messages that fail after N retries
  are moved here for investigation.
  Prevents poison-pill blocking.
end note

note bottom of offset
  Kafka: consumers track their own
  offset per partition.
  Allows independent replay / rewind.
end note

@enduml

